1 and prioritized by the Department of Transportation in accordance
2 with the criteria provided for in this subsection.
3 B. Bridges proposed for reconstruction will be generally
4 evaluated based on the state of project innovation, readiness,
5 structural adequacy, safety, serviceability, functional
6 obsolescence, essentiality for public use, and special reductions
7 for characteristics such as detour length, traffic safety features,
8 and current school bus routes.
9 C. The direct or indirect financial participation by the county
10 proposing the project shall be an additional selection factor for
11 proposed projects, along with the objective distribution of funding.
12 D. Any approved projects awarded by the Transportation
13 Commission shall be contracted as provided by law.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
15 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
16 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
17 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
18 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
